1
00:01:37,063 --> 00:01:38,031
Why aren't you home yet?

2
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:40,533
I...

3
00:01:44,237 --> 00:01:45,438
I wanted to

4
00:01:45,839 --> 00:01:46,306
apologize to you.

5
00:01:47,874 --> 00:01:49,275
I was wrong that day.

6
00:01:49,309 --> 00:01:50,543
I shouldn't have said those things.

7
00:01:50,810 --> 00:01:51,511
But deep down,

8
00:01:51,511 --> 00:01:52,278
I really didn't mean them.

9
00:01:53,246 --> 00:01:53,847
Go home.

10
00:01:54,681 --> 00:01:55,748
You must be exhausted after the surgery.

11
00:01:58,251 --> 00:01:58,852
What about you?

12
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:00,787
You heard just now.

13
00:02:01,554 --> 00:02:02,722
For the next 48 hours,

14
00:02:02,789 --> 00:02:04,157
the head nurse and I both have to stay on duty.

15
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:05,692
And Director Ji

16
00:02:05,959 --> 00:02:06,993
was someone I finally managed

17
00:02:07,026 --> 00:02:08,128
to invite here through the head nurse.

18
00:02:08,628 --> 00:02:09,729
I still want to learn more from her.

19
00:03:22,368 --> 00:03:23,703
He's already on lipid-lowering medication.

20
00:03:23,803 --> 00:03:25,205
Why are his lipids still rising?

21
00:03:26,206 --> 00:03:27,240
I find it strange too.

22
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:33,746
Can I see all his test reports

23
00:03:33,746 --> 00:03:35,215
since admission?

24
00:03:35,682 --> 00:03:36,049
Of course.

25
00:03:36,149 --> 00:03:36,816
Come with me.

26
00:03:47,894 --> 00:03:48,161
Here.

27
00:03:48,695 --> 00:03:49,362
When did he

28
00:03:49,395 --> 00:03:50,597
start receiving sedatives?

29
00:03:51,664 --> 00:03:52,532
Let me check.

30
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:53,933
Here.

31
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,874
It could be propofol infusion syndrome.

32
00:04:02,108 --> 00:04:03,142
Try adjusting the sedation.

33
00:04:03,910 --> 00:04:04,544
Propofol?

34
00:04:05,478 --> 00:04:06,279
Switch to midazolam.

35
00:04:06,846 --> 00:04:07,213
Okay.

36
00:04:11,517 --> 00:04:12,752
His triglycerides are elevated.

37
00:04:13,319 --> 00:04:14,187
He also has mild hypotension.

38
00:04:19,525 --> 00:04:20,393
During handover just now,

39
00:04:20,393 --> 00:04:21,427
did you see

40
00:04:21,427 --> 00:04:22,595
Director Sheng's face?

41
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:25,665
He looked like

42
00:04:26,366 --> 00:04:27,967
a pressure cooker on mute.

43
00:04:28,568 --> 00:04:29,969
Completely calm on the surface,

44
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:30,903
but

45
00:04:31,304 --> 00:04:33,072
ready to explode at any moment.

46
00:04:33,306 --> 00:04:33,873
It was terrifying.

47
00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:35,208
Bro,

48
00:04:35,675 --> 00:04:36,643
do you think it's possible

49
00:04:36,743 --> 00:04:37,910
Director Sheng believes we were

50
00:04:38,111 --> 00:04:38,945
trying to save the patient,

51
00:04:39,345 --> 00:04:40,480
so he won't pursue it?

52
00:04:40,813 --> 00:04:41,881
I have a suggestion.

53
00:04:42,515 --> 00:04:43,650
If you're not using that brain,

54
00:04:43,683 --> 00:04:44,684
why not donate it?

55
00:04:44,884 --> 00:04:45,685
It must be exhausting carrying it around.

56
00:04:46,085 --> 00:04:46,786
You stole

57
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:47,854
the department director's surgery,

58
00:04:48,087 --> 00:04:49,288
and now you expect him to praise you?

59
00:04:49,589 --> 00:04:50,390
Why don't you go ask him

60
00:04:50,556 --> 00:04:51,524
for a gold star?

61
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:53,993
Right now, I just hope

62
00:04:54,327 --> 00:04:55,962
Boss Sheng loses his temper.

63
00:04:56,195 --> 00:04:57,163
Slams the table,

64
00:04:57,597 --> 00:04:58,197
curses us,

65
00:04:58,765 --> 00:04:59,399
fines us,

66
00:04:59,432 --> 00:05:00,466
or gives us a disciplinary penalty.

67
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:01,434
That would mean

68
00:05:01,434 --> 00:05:02,268
the sentence had been handed down.

69
00:05:02,769 --> 00:05:04,637
At worst, it's just a scar after the beheading.

70
00:05:04,771 --> 00:05:05,438
But what does this mean now?

71
00:05:05,605 --> 00:05:06,272
It's still hanging over us.

72
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:07,807
That's terrifying.

73
00:05:08,441 --> 00:05:09,409
When punishment is unpredictable

74
00:05:09,676 --> 00:05:10,476
and authority immeasurable,

75
00:05:10,743 --> 00:05:11,911
the people fear those above them.

76
00:05:12,745 --> 00:05:14,347
A storm is brewing.

77
00:05:21,254 --> 00:05:22,322
President Wang. Director Sheng.

78
00:05:22,989 --> 00:05:23,523
I'm sorry.

79
00:05:24,524 --> 00:05:25,758
Yesterday, the situation was urgent.

80
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:27,193
To save the patient,

81
00:05:27,727 --> 00:05:29,162
I failed to report promptly to the hospital

82
00:05:29,595 --> 00:05:30,563
or communicate with Director Sheng,

83
00:05:31,130 --> 00:05:32,365
and temporarily changed the lead surgeon.

84
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:34,567
Procedurally,

85
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:35,935
it was indeed highly improper.

86
00:05:36,669 --> 00:05:38,371
You're avoiding the real issue.

87
00:05:39,305 --> 00:05:40,406
Changing the lead surgeon at the last minute,

88
00:05:40,606 --> 00:05:41,974
disregarding the patient's interests,

89
00:05:42,308 --> 00:05:43,076
rashly interfering

90
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:44,343
in another department's work,

91
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:46,746
and showing contempt for colleagues and leadership.

92
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:47,914
Zhou Xiaofeng,

93
00:05:48,614 --> 00:05:49,348
aren't you far too arrogant?

94
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:51,851
Even if we disagreed

95
00:05:51,918 --> 00:05:52,385
on the surgical plan,

96
00:05:53,052 --> 00:05:53,753
you still couldn't

97
00:05:53,853 --> 00:05:55,288
humiliate me like that.

98
00:05:56,756 --> 00:05:57,390
An apology like this—

99
00:05:58,157 --> 00:05:58,725
I don't accept it.

100
00:06:09,502 --> 00:06:10,203
I'll get back to work.

101
00:06:21,814 --> 00:06:22,248
Everyone,

102
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:26,519
before today's regular meeting,

103
00:06:27,186 --> 00:06:28,321
let's first have Director Zhou

104
00:06:29,489 --> 00:06:32,325
explain exactly what happened.

105
00:06:39,465 --> 00:06:39,966
Yesterday,

106
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:42,769
Cardiology patient Du Yan

107
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:44,837
developed acute heart failure

108
00:06:45,037 --> 00:06:46,172
in the general ICU.

109
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:49,642
Because of my own subjective judgment,

110
00:06:51,344 --> 00:06:52,845
I abused my authority as the attending physician.

111
00:06:54,947 --> 00:06:55,948
Without prior consultation

112
00:06:56,015 --> 00:06:56,949
or communication,

113
00:06:57,950 --> 00:06:59,185
and without reporting to my superior,

114
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:01,554
I removed Director Sheng as lead surgeon.

115
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:03,589
This was extremely disrespectful

116
00:07:04,123 --> 00:07:05,091
to Director Sheng

117
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:07,960
and irresponsible toward the patient.

118
00:07:09,295 --> 00:07:09,729
Therefore,

119
00:07:11,330 --> 00:07:12,665
I would like, in front of everyone,

120
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:16,502
to formally apologize to Director Sheng.

121
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:17,904
I'm sorry.

122
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:25,478
Director Zhou, that's too serious.

123
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:28,514
My main concern was still the patient.

124
00:07:30,082 --> 00:07:31,384
After all, I understood

125
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:32,318
the original surgical plan best.

126
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:34,287
If the lead surgeon

127
00:07:34,387 --> 00:07:35,288
and surgical plan were both changed,

128
00:07:35,755 --> 00:07:36,689
and something went wrong,

129
00:07:37,156 --> 00:07:37,790
then what?

130
00:07:38,591 --> 00:07:39,192
Right?

131
00:07:44,530 --> 00:07:45,398
Director Sheng is right.

132
00:07:46,866 --> 00:07:47,400
But

133
00:07:48,167 --> 00:07:48,968
I ask Director Sheng

134
00:07:49,869 --> 00:07:50,670
not to hold the other

135
00:07:50,770 --> 00:07:51,904
colleagues who participated accountable.

136
00:07:52,872 --> 00:07:53,906
I forced all of them

137
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:54,807
to join the surgery.

138
00:07:57,743 --> 00:07:58,311
Director Zhou,

139
00:07:59,846 --> 00:08:01,013
you don't need to plead for them.

140
00:08:01,714 --> 00:08:02,348
Cardiac Surgery

141
00:08:02,348 --> 00:08:03,182
has its own rules.

142
00:08:06,552 --> 00:08:08,054
I hope every

143
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,322
Cardiac Surgery colleague here

144
00:08:09,755 --> 00:08:11,757
reflects on this incident.

145
00:08:12,792 --> 00:08:15,127
Completing the surgery was our duty.

146
00:08:16,095 --> 00:08:17,430
But when faced with such hasty

147
00:08:17,463 --> 00:08:18,865
and unreasonable command,

148
00:08:19,799 --> 00:08:20,967
you let so-called team spirit

149
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,202
cloud your judgment and acted blindly,

150
00:08:24,003 --> 00:08:25,238
ignoring regulations and procedures,

151
00:08:25,304 --> 00:08:26,439
and disregarding the patient's interests.

152
00:08:26,672 --> 00:08:27,773
This was complete chaos.

153
00:08:29,609 --> 00:08:30,643
I was the lead surgeon.

154
00:08:36,115 --> 00:08:37,583
Cardiac Surgery has always followed

155
00:08:38,050 --> 00:08:38,784
the lead-surgeon responsibility system.

156
00:08:40,119 --> 00:08:42,054
So as lead surgeon, Lin Yi

157
00:08:42,522 --> 00:08:43,489
must bear full responsibility

158
00:08:43,789 --> 00:08:44,557
for this incident.

159
00:08:48,127 --> 00:08:48,761
I now announce

160
00:08:48,794 --> 00:08:49,996
Cardiac Surgery's disciplinary decision.

161
00:08:50,663 --> 00:08:52,965
Lin Yi will receive an official reprimand

162
00:08:53,666 --> 00:08:54,767
and must submit

163
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:55,835
a thorough written self-criticism within two days.

164
00:09:02,475 --> 00:09:03,009
I accept.

165
00:09:06,512 --> 00:09:07,246
Also, Dr. Fang,

166
00:09:12,151 --> 00:09:12,985
Du Yan was transferred

167
00:09:13,052 --> 00:09:13,686
from your general ICU

168
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:14,787
into the operating room.

169
00:09:15,922 --> 00:09:17,189
He is now still

170
00:09:17,189 --> 00:09:17,757
in the general ICU.

171
00:09:19,558 --> 00:09:20,960
All eyes are on you.

172
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:22,428
If anything goes wrong

173
00:09:22,428 --> 00:09:23,262
with his postoperative care,

174
00:09:23,663 --> 00:09:24,630
you will be the first person held responsible.

175
00:09:25,364 --> 00:09:25,765
Do you understand?

176
00:09:27,366 --> 00:09:27,833
Understood.

177
00:09:29,902 --> 00:09:30,236
President,

178
00:09:31,437 --> 00:09:32,238
this is our department's

179
00:09:32,271 --> 00:09:34,473
disciplinary plan for the incident.

180
00:09:38,878 --> 00:09:39,245
That's all.

181
00:09:47,053 --> 00:09:47,353
Sit down.

182
00:09:48,688 --> 00:09:49,455
Both of you, sit.

183
00:09:55,027 --> 00:09:56,596
Does this mean we've passed?

184
00:09:56,629 --> 00:09:57,763
Du Yan's surgery was successful.

185
00:09:57,763 --> 00:09:58,364
It appears so.

186
00:09:58,531 --> 00:09:59,732
That deserves recognition.

187
00:10:00,566 --> 00:10:01,367
But Director Zhou,

188
00:10:01,801 --> 00:10:02,835
as department director,

189
00:10:03,402 --> 00:10:04,470
you are responsible

190
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:06,572
for the strategy and command

191
00:10:06,639 --> 00:10:07,673
of the entire team.

192
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:10,142
You must protect

193
00:10:10,209 --> 00:10:10,943
the patient's life,

194
00:10:11,677 --> 00:10:13,212
follow scientific guidelines

195
00:10:13,546 --> 00:10:15,147
and institutional regulations,

196
00:10:15,715 --> 00:10:17,249
and set

197
00:10:17,516 --> 00:10:18,651
a good example for the team.

198
00:10:19,151 --> 00:10:21,153
You cannot make biased decisions

199
00:10:21,554 --> 00:10:23,456
on a momentary impulse.

200
00:10:27,927 --> 00:10:29,729
As for Director Zhou's punishment,

201
00:10:30,229 --> 00:10:32,565
we will await the Party committee's decision

202
00:10:33,132 --> 00:10:34,200
and enforce it accordingly.

203
00:10:41,407 --> 00:10:42,074
Does anyone else

204
00:10:42,775 --> 00:10:43,609
have anything to add?

205
00:10:45,711 --> 00:10:46,612
If not,

206
00:10:48,014 --> 00:10:50,016
we'll continue the regular meeting.

207
00:10:52,752 --> 00:10:53,152
Bro,

208
00:11:00,159 --> 00:11:02,028
you took all the consequences.

209
00:11:02,795 --> 00:11:03,195
It's fine.

210
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:05,264
You don't need to worry about me.

211
00:11:05,398 --> 00:11:06,198
There won't be a problem.

212
00:11:07,199 --> 00:11:08,634
You saw what happened with Lin Yi.

213
00:11:08,968 --> 00:11:09,635
Sheng Nian won't really

214
00:11:09,668 --> 00:11:10,369
make an example of him.

215
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:11,837
But you yourself

216
00:11:12,304 --> 00:11:13,239
need to be more careful.

217
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:14,774
The burden of caring for Du Yan

218
00:11:15,041 --> 00:11:16,308
is now on your shoulders.

219
00:11:16,909 --> 00:11:17,910
Don't worry about me.

220
00:11:18,244 --> 00:11:19,245
Even without him saying so,

221
00:11:19,278 --> 00:11:20,312
I would take good care of Du Yan.

222
00:11:22,348 --> 00:11:23,315
I'll get back to work.

223
00:11:27,119 --> 00:11:27,586
Bro.

224
00:11:29,255 --> 00:11:31,023
He has an MRI this afternoon.

225
00:11:31,624 --> 00:11:32,324
When the time comes,

226
00:11:33,025 --> 00:11:34,226
remember to remind him.

227
00:11:53,646 --> 00:11:55,214
So? Satisfied?

228
00:11:59,185 --> 00:12:01,087
I have no objection to the punishment.

229
00:12:01,587 --> 00:12:02,655
I'll take responsibility for what I did.

230
00:12:02,922 --> 00:12:03,722
I was the one who dragged everyone

231
00:12:03,756 --> 00:12:04,490
into the operating room.

232
00:12:05,324 --> 00:12:07,426
The lead-surgeon responsibility system is fair.

233
00:12:09,495 --> 00:12:10,629
That's not what I meant.

234
00:12:12,164 --> 00:12:13,132
I meant the surgery.

235
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:22,241
The surgery went very smoothly.

236
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:23,509
I'm very satisfied.

237
00:12:29,215 --> 00:12:29,782
I know.

238
00:12:30,716 --> 00:12:31,550
Given the situation then,

239
00:12:32,384 --> 00:12:33,753
you were the only one who could lead it.

240
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:36,455
I'm glad it was you.

241
00:12:37,389 --> 00:12:38,124
Anyone else

242
00:12:38,624 --> 00:12:39,425
couldn't have done

243
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:40,493
Du Yan's surgery that well.

244
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:46,065
Thank you for understanding, Director.

245
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:22,401
Hello?

246
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:24,770
He's being examined now.

247
00:13:26,272 --> 00:13:26,605
Okay.

248
00:13:26,972 --> 00:13:28,207
I'll tell you as soon as it's finished.

249
00:13:37,683 --> 00:13:38,651
You big idiot.

250
00:13:39,685 --> 00:13:40,853
You said such harsh things that day,

251
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,288
yet Xiaoran is still worried about you.

252
00:14:08,113 --> 00:14:09,315
We've always treated you like family.

253
00:14:10,482 --> 00:14:11,917
I want to become your family too.

254
00:14:13,652 --> 00:14:13,986
What about you?

255
00:14:15,187 --> 00:14:16,488
All my family is dead.

256
00:14:29,134 --> 00:14:30,369
I don't believe

257
00:14:30,402 --> 00:14:31,036
you meant what you said that day.

258
00:14:33,973 --> 00:14:35,007
But if you choose

259
00:14:35,007 --> 00:14:35,674
to keep going like this,

260
00:14:37,109 --> 00:14:38,410
I have nothing more to say.

261
00:14:42,514 --> 00:14:43,315
No matter what,

262
00:14:47,119 --> 00:14:48,287
you must stay healthy

263
00:14:49,755 --> 00:14:50,489
and live to a hundred.

264
00:15:07,706 --> 00:15:08,841
His lipids are finally coming down.

265
00:15:10,209 --> 00:15:10,809
That's great.

266
00:15:11,277 --> 00:15:12,945
Dr. Fang, you really did it.

267
00:15:13,112 --> 00:15:14,446
In all my years of work,

268
00:15:14,613 --> 00:15:15,514
I've rarely encountered

269
00:15:15,614 --> 00:15:16,749
propofol infusion syndrome.

270
00:15:17,216 --> 00:15:18,350
We really owe it to Director Ji.

271
00:15:18,784 --> 00:15:19,952
Propofol infusion syndrome

272
00:15:20,052 --> 00:15:21,387
was something I'd only read about.

273
00:15:21,687 --> 00:15:22,488
It's a rare

274
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:23,956
but highly fatal

275
00:15:23,989 --> 00:15:24,923
adverse drug reaction.

276
00:15:25,224 --> 00:15:26,558
If we hadn't caught it in time,

277
00:15:26,825 --> 00:15:28,127
the consequences would've been unthinkable.

278
00:15:28,694 --> 00:15:29,028
In our

279
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:30,229
intensive care unit,

280
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:31,163
we treat critically ill patients

281
00:15:31,263 --> 00:15:32,564
from multiple specialties.

282
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:34,867
Many require prolonged

283
00:15:34,967 --> 00:15:36,068
propofol sedation.

284
00:15:36,435 --> 00:15:38,404
And long-term, high-dose use

285
00:15:38,637 --> 00:15:40,005
can affect lipid levels.

286
00:15:40,372 --> 00:15:41,507
There is always more to learn.

287
00:15:43,208 --> 00:15:44,443
Dr. Fang is so young,

288
00:15:44,476 --> 00:15:45,811
yet already outstanding.

289
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:48,247
After observing her all night,

290
00:15:48,514 --> 00:15:49,014
I realized

291
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:50,082
she is actually

292
00:15:50,349 --> 00:15:50,883
a very promising candidate

293
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:52,318
for our ICU too.

294
00:15:52,851 --> 00:15:53,852
You're too kind.

295
00:15:53,952 --> 00:15:54,687
Director Ji,

296
00:15:55,087 --> 00:15:55,521
what's this?

297
00:15:55,688 --> 00:15:56,922
Are you trying to poach her from us?

298
00:15:57,823 --> 00:15:58,791
You caught me.

299
00:16:08,267 --> 00:16:08,634
It's fine.

300
00:16:09,368 --> 00:16:10,135
There hasn't been

301
00:16:10,135 --> 00:16:10,970
any notable progression.

302
00:16:12,805 --> 00:16:13,372
It's so noisy.

303
00:16:13,439 --> 00:16:14,206
All that buzzing,

304
00:16:16,675 --> 00:16:17,609
and people talking too.

305
00:16:18,277 --> 00:16:19,545
Even louder than the MRI.

306
00:16:22,548 --> 00:16:23,282
Can I leave now?

307
00:16:31,557 --> 00:16:33,025
"Live to a hundred" is my line.

308
00:16:35,027 --> 00:16:35,794
You need my permission

309
00:16:35,828 --> 00:16:36,729
before using it.

310
00:16:43,736 --> 00:16:44,503
You big idiot.

311
00:16:53,846 --> 00:16:54,513
Director Lin.

312
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:55,347
Thank you for your hard work.

313
00:17:00,486 --> 00:17:01,320
Thank you so much.

314
00:17:10,729 --> 00:17:11,330
I checked him.

315
00:17:11,430 --> 00:17:12,431
His condition is quite stable.

316
00:17:12,931 --> 00:17:13,799
You don't need to stay here.

317
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:15,334
You can go home and rest today.

318
00:17:18,237 --> 00:17:19,204
We can't let our guard down.

319
00:17:23,008 --> 00:17:24,410
There are so many people in the ICU.

320
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:26,045
The head nurse and the others are all here.

321
00:17:29,615 --> 00:17:30,682
You can't be the only one

322
00:17:30,716 --> 00:17:31,283
watching him nonstop.

323
00:17:32,584 --> 00:17:33,952
Tonight is still critical.

324
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:35,721
I need to keep watching.

325
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:38,190
All right.

326
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:41,326
Then...

327
00:17:43,529 --> 00:17:44,730
will you go home tomorrow night?

328
00:17:48,634 --> 00:17:49,868
We'll see tomorrow.

329
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:27,840
Look at Director Lin,

330
00:18:28,073 --> 00:18:28,841
glancing around everywhere,

331
00:18:28,907 --> 00:18:30,042
completely distracted.

332
00:18:32,144 --> 00:18:33,145
And Teacher Fang

333
00:18:33,245 --> 00:18:34,213
has barely smiled lately.

334
00:18:36,748 --> 00:18:37,449
Our hospital's couple

335
00:18:37,449 --> 00:18:38,450
can't possibly be in trouble.

336
00:18:39,318 --> 00:18:40,319
I've cried so much lately

337
00:18:40,319 --> 00:18:40,752
over

338
00:18:40,752 --> 00:18:41,920
the "Maomei as Ever" couple.

339
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:42,554
the "Maomei as Ever" couple.

340
00:18:43,455 --> 00:18:44,123
What couple?

341
00:18:45,023 --> 00:18:45,757
"Maomei as Ever."

342
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:47,493
Who and who?

343
00:18:49,127 --> 00:18:50,195
Peng Mao and Jiang Huichu.

344
00:18:52,264 --> 00:18:53,031
Don't you think

345
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,166
they share one quality?

346
00:18:54,199 --> 00:18:54,867
They're both

347
00:18:55,267 --> 00:18:56,401
so pure,

348
00:18:56,435 --> 00:18:57,469
so simple,

349
00:18:57,803 --> 00:18:59,171
and so worthy of respect.

350
00:19:00,172 --> 00:19:01,073
And Teacher Peng's son

351
00:19:01,173 --> 00:19:02,474
still refuses to see him.

352
00:19:03,075 --> 00:19:04,343
If in the end

353
00:19:04,343 --> 00:19:05,477
Teacher Peng never gets to see him,

354
00:19:06,345 --> 00:19:07,079
what then?

355
00:19:07,513 --> 00:19:08,247
What can anyone do?

356
00:19:09,348 --> 00:19:10,916
Everyone has their own causes and consequences.

357
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:12,684
No matter how regrettable,

358
00:19:13,318 --> 00:19:14,119
sometimes we can only accept it.

359
00:19:17,756 --> 00:19:19,024
That's life, I suppose.

360
00:19:19,958 --> 00:19:21,760
Everyone has their own convictions,

361
00:19:23,562 --> 00:19:25,264
and therefore their own regrets.

362
00:19:27,566 --> 00:19:30,068
For him, living like this is worse than death.

363
00:19:31,036 --> 00:19:31,904
But because

364
00:19:32,271 --> 00:19:33,772
he still has something he can't let go of,

365
00:19:34,439 --> 00:19:36,642
he keeps clinging

366
00:19:37,509 --> 00:19:38,810
It's too painful.

367
00:20:08,974 --> 00:20:09,308
Does it hurt?

368
00:20:10,008 --> 00:20:10,409
No.

369
00:20:11,543 --> 00:20:12,878
I've reviewed all your indicators.

370
00:20:13,412 --> 00:20:14,846
You're recovering very well, handsome.

371
00:20:16,281 --> 00:20:17,216
Thank you, Director Ji.

372
00:20:17,749 --> 00:20:18,383
Keep it up.

373
00:20:24,356 --> 00:20:25,724
This is your controller.

374
00:20:27,292 --> 00:20:28,160
In this bag,

375
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:29,328
there are two batteries.

376
00:20:29,928 --> 00:20:30,929
For ordinary daily movement,

377
00:20:30,996 --> 00:20:31,830
if you're not going far,

378
00:20:31,863 --> 00:20:32,664
these will be enough.

379
00:20:32,998 --> 00:20:33,999
But we'll still prepare

380
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,167
some backups for you.

381
00:20:35,801 --> 00:20:36,868
So that means

382
00:20:38,003 --> 00:20:39,037
if it runs out of power,

383
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:41,306
I run out of power too?

384
00:20:41,773 --> 00:20:42,708
Normally,

385
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:43,675
that won't happen.

386
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:45,544
I'll slowly teach you

387
00:20:45,611 --> 00:20:46,912
daily management

388
00:20:47,279 --> 00:20:48,113
and how to handle emergencies.

389
00:20:48,947 --> 00:20:49,815
Thank you, Dr. Fang.

390
00:20:53,952 --> 00:20:55,187
This battery

391
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:57,456
is bigger than I imagined.

392
00:20:58,290 --> 00:20:59,391
They'll get smaller and smaller.

393
00:20:59,791 --> 00:21:00,626
In the future,

394
00:21:01,226 --> 00:21:02,694
hopefully they can be miniaturized.

395
00:21:06,865 --> 00:21:08,066
They should make them

396
00:21:08,867 --> 00:21:09,768
solar-powered.

397
00:21:10,936 --> 00:21:11,470
That way,

398
00:21:12,471 --> 00:21:13,605
I could charge myself

399
00:21:13,905 --> 00:21:14,840
just by getting some sun.

400
00:21:16,775 --> 00:21:17,943
That's a good idea.

401
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:20,345
You'll have to develop it someday.

402
00:21:30,589 --> 00:21:31,790
The most dangerous period

403
00:21:31,790 --> 00:21:32,758
has basically passed.

404
00:21:33,725 --> 00:21:34,192
Of course,

405
00:21:34,993 --> 00:21:37,029
we still can't completely relax.

406
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:41,800
Director Ji, thank you for your hard work these past two days.

407
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:44,269
Du Yan made it safely through the critical phase,

408
00:21:44,603 --> 00:21:45,971
and I learned a great deal from you.

409
00:21:47,172 --> 00:21:47,773
Dr. Fang,

410
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:49,641
you're only in your early thirties,

411
00:21:50,208 --> 00:21:51,476
yet so calm and capable.

412
00:21:52,411 --> 00:21:52,811
Thank you.

413
00:21:53,879 --> 00:21:54,513
I can tell

414
00:21:54,746 --> 00:21:56,315
your foundation is very solid,

415
00:21:56,748 --> 00:21:58,784
and your experience far exceeds your peers.

416
00:21:58,884 --> 00:21:59,251
Not at all.

417
00:21:59,251 --> 00:22:00,118
That's truly rare.

418
00:22:01,053 --> 00:22:01,787
I never expected

419
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,455
our hospital's Heart Center

420
00:22:03,555 --> 00:22:04,756
to be hiding such an excellent

421
00:22:04,823 --> 00:22:05,957
critical-care specialist.

422
00:22:06,191 --> 00:22:07,292
You're too kind, Director Ji.

423
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:09,795
Actually, I've always wanted a chance

424
00:22:09,895 --> 00:22:11,196
to train in critical care.

425
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:13,165
The human body is like

426
00:22:13,198 --> 00:22:14,533
a precise and complex machine.

427
00:22:14,966 --> 00:22:16,134
One small detail

428
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:17,569
can cause total collapse,

429
00:22:17,869 --> 00:22:19,604
or completely turn the tide.

430
00:22:19,971 --> 00:22:20,272
Exactly.

431
00:22:21,807 --> 00:22:23,575
In terms of work,

432
00:22:23,909 --> 00:22:24,543
Critical Care Medicine

433
00:22:24,643 --> 00:22:25,344
and the general ICU

434
00:22:25,877 --> 00:22:27,012
are broad and comprehensive,

435
00:22:27,279 --> 00:22:28,246
while the Heart Center's

436
00:22:28,246 --> 00:22:28,947
ICU

437
00:22:29,314 --> 00:22:30,415
is specialized and deep.

438
00:22:30,582 --> 00:22:30,949
Exactly.

439
00:22:31,316 --> 00:22:33,151
We provide specialist support here.

440
00:22:33,552 --> 00:22:35,554
Your side is the final battlefield

441
00:22:35,687 --> 00:22:36,455
for multisystem disease.

442
00:22:36,755 --> 00:22:37,456
Exactly.

443
00:22:38,490 --> 00:22:39,491
We often say

444
00:22:39,691 --> 00:22:40,325
that doctors in Critical Care Medicine

445
00:22:40,358 --> 00:22:41,593
and the general ICU

446
00:22:41,827 --> 00:22:42,427
are each

447
00:22:42,527 --> 00:22:43,695
an army unto themselves.

448
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,798
Right, I suddenly remembered.

449
00:22:47,065 --> 00:22:48,867
Our department organized training before.

450
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:50,335
Didn't you sign up?

451
00:22:50,569 --> 00:22:51,703
But you never came.

452
00:22:53,205 --> 00:22:54,406
Yes, I did sign up.

453
00:22:54,706 --> 00:22:55,474
You still remember.

454
00:22:57,109 --> 00:22:58,276
Something came up then,

455
00:22:58,844 --> 00:22:59,611
so I missed it.

456
00:23:01,246 --> 00:23:01,847
It's all right.

457
00:23:02,414 --> 00:23:02,814
You see,

458
00:23:03,215 --> 00:23:04,082
when the timing is right,

459
00:23:04,216 --> 00:23:05,550
we still meet.

460
00:23:06,084 --> 00:23:06,518
Yes.

461
00:23:07,753 --> 00:23:08,153
All right.

462
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:09,788
Things are stable here,

463
00:23:10,088 --> 00:23:11,156
so I'll head back.

464
00:23:12,190 --> 00:23:12,791
Dr. Fang,

465
00:23:13,291 --> 00:23:14,793
it was a pleasure meeting you.

466
00:23:14,926 --> 00:23:15,494
Likewise.

467
00:23:15,894 --> 00:23:16,762
I hope we have another chance

468
00:23:16,795 --> 00:23:18,430
to fight side by side.

469
00:23:20,365 --> 00:23:20,632
Definitely.

470
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:22,167
See you, Director Ji.

471
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:22,667
See you.

472
00:23:23,335 --> 00:23:24,269
Find time to rest.

473
00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:31,510
How do you feel?

474
00:23:32,110 --> 00:23:32,844
Are you dizzy?

475
00:23:34,546 --> 00:23:35,514
Not dizzy,

476
00:23:36,681 --> 00:23:38,016
but my legs feel weak.

477
00:23:38,917 --> 00:23:39,484
That's normal.

478
00:23:39,885 --> 00:23:40,952
You look handsome and energetic.

479
00:23:43,388 --> 00:23:44,256
You probably haven't

480
00:23:44,289 --> 00:23:45,423
stood or walked for too long.

481
00:23:46,224 --> 00:23:47,726
We'll call this video

482
00:23:48,326 --> 00:23:50,395
"Rare Footage of Early Humans

483
00:23:50,529 --> 00:23:51,263
Taming Their Limbs."

484
00:23:52,664 --> 00:23:53,198
Brother Du,

485
00:23:53,965 --> 00:23:54,633
remember

486
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:55,400
to beautify me.

487
00:23:55,467 --> 00:23:55,967
I know, I know.

488
00:23:56,001 --> 00:23:56,735
The full beauty-filter package.

489
00:23:58,470 --> 00:23:59,971
After such major surgery,

490
00:24:00,071 --> 00:24:00,872
the physical trauma

491
00:24:00,972 --> 00:24:01,773
was certainly significant.

492
00:24:02,307 --> 00:24:03,375
But you've done very well

493
00:24:03,642 --> 00:24:04,543
and recovered quickly.

494
00:24:04,810 --> 00:24:06,011
In another day or two,

495
00:24:06,044 --> 00:24:07,145
you should be able to transfer to a regular ward.

496
00:24:07,445 --> 00:24:08,013
Really?

497
00:24:12,717 --> 00:24:13,185
What's wrong?

498
00:24:17,989 --> 00:24:18,523
Then...

499
00:24:19,491 --> 00:24:20,158
does that mean

500
00:24:20,225 --> 00:24:21,326
I won't see you anymore?

501
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:23,595
Of course you will.

502
00:24:23,995 --> 00:24:24,996
Of course you will.

503
00:24:25,664 --> 00:24:26,398
Just not here.

504
00:24:29,468 --> 00:24:30,602
All right, that's enough for today.

505
00:24:30,869 --> 00:24:31,803
Okay. Slowly.

506
00:24:32,704 --> 00:24:33,505
Come on, slowly.

507
00:24:34,072 --> 00:24:34,472
Careful.

508
00:24:34,673 --> 00:24:35,073
Thank you.

509
00:24:36,274 --> 00:24:36,675
Careful.

510
00:24:37,909 --> 00:24:39,344
Director Lin, you're here.

511
00:24:39,744 --> 00:24:40,245
Don't film me.

512
00:24:41,947 --> 00:24:42,814
How do you feel today?

513
00:24:43,348 --> 00:24:43,849
Pretty good.

514
00:24:44,449 --> 00:24:45,450
Today's step count

515
00:24:45,717 --> 00:24:46,985
broke one hundred.

516
00:24:47,586 --> 00:24:48,286
For recovering this quickly,

517
00:24:48,286 --> 00:24:49,287
you should thank Dr. Fang.

518
00:24:50,055 --> 00:24:51,289
She cared for you day and night

519
00:24:51,823 --> 00:24:52,424
and didn't even go home.

520
00:24:54,326 --> 00:24:55,160
Thank you, Dr. Fang.

521
00:24:59,798 --> 00:25:01,366
This feels so incredible.

522
00:25:01,766 --> 00:25:03,001
in an anime,

523
00:25:03,235 --> 00:25:04,402
with a cyberpunk

524
00:25:04,469 --> 00:25:05,670
metal heart,

525
00:25:06,071 --> 00:25:07,205
rebuilt

526
00:25:08,006 --> 00:25:08,840
and sent back out.

527
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:17,215
Iron Man.

528
00:25:22,687 --> 00:25:23,755
Is this something you like?

529
00:25:24,322 --> 00:25:24,756
What's this?

530
00:25:27,192 --> 00:25:28,793
It's always hung from my bag.

531
00:25:29,561 --> 00:25:30,428
It's my favorite.

532
00:25:31,630 --> 00:25:32,264
Do you know him?

533
00:25:34,666 --> 00:25:35,066
No.

534
00:25:36,801 --> 00:25:37,235
All right.

535
00:25:38,236 --> 00:25:39,604
There are already two seasons,

536
00:25:40,272 --> 00:25:40,906
and I heard

537
00:25:41,373 --> 00:25:42,440
the third is coming soon.

538
00:25:44,075 --> 00:25:44,943
Then recover well

539
00:25:46,077 --> 00:25:46,811
and wait for season three.

540
00:26:04,396 --> 00:26:06,131
The old gentleman in Bed 7

541
00:26:07,332 --> 00:26:08,433
seems to have passed away overnight.

542
00:26:10,268 --> 00:26:11,403
Near dawn,

543
00:26:12,470 --> 00:26:14,272
I heard his family crying outside.

544
00:26:16,408 --> 00:26:17,275
When I came in today,

545
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:19,311
the bed was empty.

546
00:26:20,679 --> 00:26:21,947
Du Yan in Bed 13,

547
00:26:22,514 --> 00:26:23,415
that young man—

548
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:24,115
do you remember him?

549
00:26:24,883 --> 00:26:26,117
His surgery was successful.

550
00:26:26,751 --> 00:26:27,986
He received an artificial heart

551
00:26:28,887 --> 00:26:30,355
and has transferred to a regular ward.

552
00:26:31,957 --> 00:26:32,724
His family

553
00:26:33,558 --> 00:26:35,126
left happily together.

554
00:26:39,364 --> 00:26:40,031
Teacher Peng,

555
00:26:41,199 --> 00:26:41,766
what about you?

556
00:26:43,201 --> 00:26:44,803
Do you want to remain here,

557
00:26:46,771 --> 00:26:47,906
or shall we go home?

558
00:26:52,010 --> 00:26:52,611
Teacher Jiang,

559
00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:54,479
someone is here to visit Teacher Peng.

560
00:26:57,749 --> 00:26:58,883
Then I'll stop the sedation first.

561
00:27:18,436 --> 00:27:19,270
Come in.

562
00:27:26,845 --> 00:27:27,679
This is Grandpa.

563
00:27:28,046 --> 00:27:29,414
Baby, say "Grandpa."

564
00:27:31,716 --> 00:27:32,083
Good girl.

565
00:27:32,550 --> 00:27:33,351
Say "Grandpa."

566
00:27:34,586 --> 00:27:35,086
Go on.

567
00:27:39,024 --> 00:27:39,758
Grandpa.

568
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:49,267
Say it.

569
00:27:50,135 --> 00:27:50,802
Grandpa.

570
00:28:00,445 --> 00:28:01,446
Hello, Grandpa.

571
00:28:32,277 --> 00:28:32,744
Baby,

572
00:28:33,011 --> 00:28:34,679
Grandpa wrote us the character "good."

573
00:28:42,387 --> 00:28:43,054
I'm here.

574
00:28:44,589 --> 00:28:45,490
I've always been here.

575
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:10,715
What are you trying to say, Teacher Peng?

576
00:29:11,683 --> 00:29:12,684
I don't understand.

577
00:29:13,384 --> 00:29:14,686
What are you trying to say?

578
00:29:16,955 --> 00:29:17,722
Teacher Peng.

579
00:29:20,992 --> 00:29:21,726
Teacher Peng.

580
00:29:23,128 --> 00:29:24,963
What are you trying to say?

581
00:29:37,308 --> 00:29:38,042
Dr. Du.

582
00:29:39,844 --> 00:29:40,445
Thank you.

583
00:29:49,087 --> 00:29:49,554
Why are you crying?

584
00:29:49,921 --> 00:29:50,655
What's wrong, Dr. Du?

585
00:29:51,556 --> 00:29:52,524
Did you call Teacher Peng's son

586
00:29:52,524 --> 00:29:53,158
again?

587
00:29:55,593 --> 00:29:57,395
I just wanted to try one more time.

588
00:29:57,929 --> 00:29:59,264
He didn't promise me anything,

589
00:29:59,931 --> 00:30:01,366
but I didn't expect

590
00:30:01,533 --> 00:30:02,600
his wife and daughter to come.

591
00:30:04,169 --> 00:30:04,769
That was thoughtful.

592
00:30:06,104 --> 00:30:06,905
Thank you, Teacher Fang.

593
00:30:08,373 --> 00:30:09,908
You taught me to always keep the patient

594
00:30:10,041 --> 00:30:10,675
in my heart.

595
00:30:12,410 --> 00:30:14,012
Then keep the patient in your heart,

596
00:30:14,112 --> 00:30:15,046
not in your eyes.

597
00:30:15,613 --> 00:30:16,948
Right, Teacher Fang?

598
00:30:18,683 --> 00:30:19,184
Come here. Let me see.

599
00:30:19,450 --> 00:30:19,851
What?

600
00:30:21,085 --> 00:30:22,053
What does this say?

601
00:30:22,554 --> 00:30:23,955
The character "good" was written by Teacher Peng

602
00:30:24,055 --> 00:30:25,223
for his granddaughter.

603
00:30:25,423 --> 00:30:26,491
And this character

604
00:30:26,624 --> 00:30:27,725
was written for Teacher Jiang.

605
00:30:27,759 --> 00:30:29,294
But we couldn't recognize it.

606
00:30:29,561 --> 00:30:31,062
What character is it?

607
00:30:57,322 --> 00:30:58,122
The examination is done. No problems.

608
00:30:58,256 --> 00:30:58,823
Get plenty of rest.

609
00:30:59,290 --> 00:30:59,691
Thank you.

610
00:31:02,760 --> 00:31:03,228
Du Yan.

611
00:31:03,761 --> 00:31:04,262
Dr. Fang.

612
00:31:04,629 --> 00:31:05,330
Sister Xiaoran.

613
00:31:05,964 --> 00:31:06,598
How do you feel?

614
00:31:07,131 --> 00:31:07,732
Pretty good.

615
00:31:08,399 --> 00:31:09,033
Why are you here?

616
00:31:09,968 --> 00:31:10,602
Didn't you ask

617
00:31:10,735 --> 00:31:11,803
when we'd meet again?

618
00:31:11,903 --> 00:31:12,704
So I came to see you.

619
00:31:13,004 --> 00:31:14,239
And we had an agreement:

620
00:31:14,372 --> 00:31:15,006
when you got better,

621
00:31:15,173 --> 00:31:16,708
I'd treat you to the food in our cafeteria.

622
00:31:17,175 --> 00:31:17,809
Thank you, sis.

623
00:31:18,276 --> 00:31:19,410
By the way, this is

624
00:31:19,444 --> 00:31:20,745
the product representative

625
00:31:20,845 --> 00:31:21,646
for the artificial heart you're using.

626
00:31:21,646 --> 00:31:22,347
Sister Ouyang.

627
00:31:22,881 --> 00:31:23,314
Hello, sis.

628
00:31:23,681 --> 00:31:24,082
Hello.

629
00:31:24,249 --> 00:31:25,083
I came to see you

630
00:31:25,283 --> 00:31:26,484
and congratulate you on your recovery.

631
00:31:27,118 --> 00:31:28,086
Let me check your driveline.

632
00:31:28,553 --> 00:31:28,853
Okay.

633
00:31:35,493 --> 00:31:36,494
It's healing well.

634
00:31:36,628 --> 00:31:37,428
Be sure to disinfect it carefully

635
00:31:37,495 --> 00:31:38,129
and protect it.

636
00:31:39,664 --> 00:31:40,164
Don't worry.

637
00:31:40,665 --> 00:31:41,132
Sister Xiaoran,

638
00:31:41,199 --> 00:31:42,133
they've already told me everything.

639
00:31:44,569 --> 00:31:45,303
Where are your parents?

640
00:31:45,770 --> 00:31:47,038
My dad went out to take a call.

641
00:31:47,572 --> 00:31:48,273
My mom

642
00:31:49,374 --> 00:31:50,375
went home to make pigeon soup.

643
00:31:53,478 --> 00:31:54,245
She won't change.

644
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:55,546
But

645
00:31:55,713 --> 00:31:57,048
I've accepted

646
00:31:57,215 --> 00:31:58,449
that she won't change.

647
00:31:59,984 --> 00:32:01,519
I won't try to

648
00:32:01,519 --> 00:32:02,320
change her mind anymore,

649
00:32:02,854 --> 00:32:04,355
and I won't drive myself crazy over it.

650
00:32:06,124 --> 00:32:06,824
I've figured it out.

651
00:32:07,492 --> 00:32:08,927
Why punish myself

652
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:09,894
for their obsession?

653
00:32:11,796 --> 00:32:13,131
A person with a steel heart

654
00:32:13,164 --> 00:32:14,032
really is different.

655
00:32:16,868 --> 00:32:17,969
Director Zhou, Director Lin,

656
00:32:18,670 --> 00:32:19,570
don't you have a meeting?

657
00:32:20,104 --> 00:32:20,705
There's still time.

658
00:32:21,572 --> 00:32:22,073
How do you feel?

659
00:32:22,307 --> 00:32:22,874
Pretty good.

660
00:32:23,875 --> 00:32:25,443
Why is it so lively here today?

661
00:32:33,584 --> 00:32:34,886
Pretty good. You're recovering well.

662
00:32:39,324 --> 00:32:40,291
The mechanical sound is regular,

663
00:32:40,725 --> 00:32:41,693
and there are no abnormal lung sounds.

664
00:32:41,960 --> 00:32:42,694
You're recovering very well.

665
00:32:43,328 --> 00:32:43,928
Thank you, Director Lin.

666
00:32:47,131 --> 00:32:47,765
What's this?

667
00:32:49,334 --> 00:32:50,735
Jin Miao gave it to me.

668
00:32:51,402 --> 00:32:52,437
A rebirth gift.

669
00:32:54,772 --> 00:32:56,507
I gave my artificial heart

670
00:32:56,641 --> 00:32:57,408
a name.

671
00:32:57,742 --> 00:32:59,143
It's called Little Lotus Root.

672
00:32:59,711 --> 00:33:01,012
Nezha was reborn from lotus roots.

673
00:33:01,279 --> 00:33:02,814
I was reborn with a mechanical heart.

674
00:33:03,114 --> 00:33:04,849
Now I have three heads and six arms.

675
00:33:06,384 --> 00:33:06,985
Congratulations.

676
00:33:07,485 --> 00:33:08,753
You're an adult

677
00:33:08,853 --> 00:33:09,287
in every sense now.

678
00:33:09,721 --> 00:33:10,154
Exactly.

679
00:33:10,888 --> 00:33:12,323
Once I recover,

680
00:33:12,724 --> 00:33:13,891
I'll take the college entrance exam,

681
00:33:14,492 --> 00:33:16,160
get into university, and fly away.

682
00:33:16,561 --> 00:33:17,195
One day,

683
00:33:18,029 --> 00:33:18,997
I'll take back control

684
00:33:18,997 --> 00:33:19,964
of my own life.

685
00:33:24,268 --> 00:33:24,802
You can do it.

686
00:33:26,504 --> 00:33:28,239
Du Yan is doing so well.

687
00:33:28,406 --> 00:33:30,074
He's like a different person from before surgery.

688
00:33:30,475 --> 00:33:30,875
Yes.

689
00:33:31,075 --> 00:33:31,743
Of course.

690
00:33:31,743 --> 00:33:32,643
Look who

691
00:33:32,643 --> 00:33:33,678
performed his surgery.

692
00:33:40,852 --> 00:33:42,553
Patients with artificial hearts

693
00:33:42,754 --> 00:33:43,955
don't only face

694
00:33:43,955 --> 00:33:44,889
physical inconvenience.

695
00:33:45,189 --> 00:33:47,759
The psychological and emotional adjustment

696
00:33:47,792 --> 00:33:48,426
is even harder.

697
00:33:49,093 --> 00:33:50,294
But Du Yan has done amazingly.

698
00:33:50,628 --> 00:33:50,995
Yes.

699
00:33:51,429 --> 00:33:52,530
It's like being reborn from the ashes.

700
00:33:52,864 --> 00:33:54,198
Only now do I realize

701
00:33:54,332 --> 00:33:55,400
gene mutations

702
00:33:55,466 --> 00:33:56,000
can cause

703
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:57,035
so many cardiomyopathies.

704
00:33:58,770 --> 00:33:59,704
How is Senlin?

705
00:34:01,839 --> 00:34:03,007
About the same.

706
00:34:03,107 --> 00:34:04,175
I've been doing everything I can.

707
00:34:04,642 --> 00:34:05,410
You both know

708
00:34:06,144 --> 00:34:07,612
all my effort can only

709
00:34:07,612 --> 00:34:08,212
slow

710
00:34:08,246 --> 00:34:09,013
the progression of his disease.

711
00:34:09,881 --> 00:34:11,149
Didn't Professor Zhang say

712
00:34:11,816 --> 00:34:12,950
that advances in gene editing

713
00:34:13,317 --> 00:34:14,285
might one day

714
00:34:14,652 --> 00:34:15,353
make a single injection

715
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:16,754
a cure?

716
00:34:17,388 --> 00:34:18,356
I've recently read

717
00:34:18,456 --> 00:34:19,390
some papers on it.

718
00:34:19,791 --> 00:34:21,159
Experts have already demonstrated

719
00:34:21,325 --> 00:34:22,527
that in vivo base editing

720
00:34:22,794 --> 00:34:24,028
can cure hypertrophic

721
00:34:24,095 --> 00:34:24,796
cardiomyopathy.

722
00:34:25,396 --> 00:34:25,997
I saw

723
00:34:26,998 --> 00:34:27,765
that study too.

724
00:34:28,066 --> 00:34:29,467
It offers a new paradigm

725
00:34:29,634 --> 00:34:30,735
for gene therapy in hypertrophic cardiomyopathy,

726
00:34:31,269 --> 00:34:32,503
and may eventually extend

727
00:34:32,570 --> 00:34:33,704
to more genetic heart diseases.

728
00:34:34,105 --> 00:34:34,806
Don't give up hope.

729
00:34:35,206 --> 00:34:35,840
I won't.

730
00:34:36,774 --> 00:34:37,875
Order 67, your coffee is ready.

731
00:34:38,242 --> 00:34:38,676
I'll get it.

732
00:34:46,117 --> 00:34:47,351
I suddenly have an idea.

733
00:34:47,785 --> 00:34:48,719
Aren't the three of you

734
00:34:48,753 --> 00:34:49,720
a team?

735
00:34:50,154 --> 00:34:51,489
You could continue researching

736
00:34:51,522 --> 00:34:52,290
this topic.

737
00:34:52,557 --> 00:34:53,958
I could even help with the groundwork.

738
00:34:55,827 --> 00:34:56,627
It's a good idea.

739
00:34:57,495 --> 00:34:58,863
But gene-research projects

740
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:00,198
are usually at provincial or ministerial level or above.

741
00:35:00,465 --> 00:35:01,132
They're very difficult to obtain.

742
00:35:01,432 --> 00:35:02,533
And starting from scratch

743
00:35:02,667 --> 00:35:04,001
requires enormous manpower and funding.

744
00:35:04,469 --> 00:35:05,403
With just the few of us,

745
00:35:06,270 --> 00:35:07,705
it would be like trying to push

746
00:35:07,772 --> 00:35:08,473
a heavy truck with our bare hands.

747
00:35:08,773 --> 00:35:09,440
Almost impossible.

748
00:35:10,775 --> 00:35:11,976
I've always followed the field.

749
00:35:12,410 --> 00:35:13,611
Hopefully one day

750
00:35:13,911 --> 00:35:15,112
we can move that truck.

751
00:35:16,714 --> 00:35:17,248
Here's the coffee.

752
00:35:18,950 --> 00:35:19,884
Why did you buy only three cups?

753
00:35:20,551 --> 00:35:21,786
They're for you three. I don't drink coffee.

754
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:23,087
You bought mine for me.

755
00:35:23,688 --> 00:35:24,755
Then I'll buy you one too.

756
00:35:31,496 --> 00:35:31,896
Thank you.

757
00:35:32,363 --> 00:35:33,397
There's cake too. Want some?

758
00:35:35,333 --> 00:35:35,766
No.

759
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:36,267
Chocolate.

760
00:35:37,235 --> 00:35:37,668
Strawberry.

761
00:35:49,280 --> 00:35:49,747
What are you doing?

762
00:35:52,917 --> 00:35:53,551
Improving myself.

763
00:35:54,585 --> 00:35:55,520
Improving yourself by drawing?

764
00:36:03,828 --> 00:36:04,195
Hello?

765
00:36:04,529 --> 00:36:05,329
Director, I'm going to the ward.

766
00:37:07,024 --> 00:37:07,592
Teacher Jiang.

767
00:37:47,598 --> 00:37:48,432
Peng Mao.

768
00:37:50,768 --> 00:37:51,602
I'm here.

769
00:37:58,643 --> 00:38:00,344
You won't hurt anymore.

770
00:38:02,947 --> 00:38:04,248
You won't suffer anymore.

771
00:38:06,884 --> 00:38:07,918
Just walk toward

772
00:38:12,123 --> 00:38:14,125
the place with light.

773
00:38:15,326 --> 00:38:16,227
Walk slowly.

774
00:38:19,530 --> 00:38:20,965
I'll stay with you.

775
00:38:24,568 --> 00:38:25,670
Walk slowly.

776
00:38:30,641 --> 00:38:31,442
Braised lion's head meatballs.

777
00:38:31,876 --> 00:38:33,344
My favorite.

778
00:38:42,286 --> 00:38:42,887
Don't worry.

779
00:38:45,690 --> 00:38:46,724
We've already chosen

780
00:38:46,724 --> 00:38:47,425
our burial plot.

781
00:38:48,025 --> 00:38:49,226
Together in life,

782
00:38:50,194 --> 00:38:51,128
together in death.

783
00:39:04,408 --> 00:39:04,875
Peng Mao.

784
00:39:05,810 --> 00:39:06,544
Time of death:

785
00:39:07,545 --> 00:39:08,679
December 29,

786
00:39:09,113 --> 00:39:10,514
2:38 p.m.

787
00:39:28,766 --> 00:39:29,233
Teacher Jiang,

788
00:39:30,601 --> 00:39:31,202
look at this.

789
00:39:37,241 --> 00:39:38,509
What your husband left behind

790
00:39:39,543 --> 00:39:40,311
wasn't a single character.

791
00:40:00,064 --> 00:40:02,199
Thank you too.

792
00:40:13,611 --> 00:40:13,944
Slowly.

793
00:40:14,078 --> 00:40:14,512
Slowly.

794
00:40:23,687 --> 00:40:24,989
Once I recover,

795
00:40:25,523 --> 00:40:26,524
I'll take the college entrance exam,

796
00:40:27,224 --> 00:40:28,959
get into university, and fly away.

797
00:40:30,795 --> 00:40:31,495
One day,

798
00:40:32,363 --> 00:40:32,963
I'll take back

799
00:40:32,963 --> 00:40:34,265
control of my own life.

800
00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:32,623
Even after a hundred years together, we must part.

801
00:41:34,191 --> 00:41:36,026
In this life, Teacher Peng and I

802
00:41:36,994 --> 00:41:37,895
have no regrets

803
00:41:38,596 --> 00:41:39,663
about each other.

804
00:42:14,265 --> 00:42:15,032
What's wrong, bro?

805
00:42:15,432 --> 00:42:15,966
What good news?

806
00:42:17,134 --> 00:42:18,168
Didn't you get the message?

807
00:42:21,405 --> 00:42:22,439
The bonus has been deposited.

808
00:42:22,606 --> 00:42:23,641
Sisi, check your phone.

809
00:42:30,681 --> 00:42:31,749
We're rich!

810
00:42:31,849 --> 00:42:32,349
That's a lot.

811
00:42:33,183 --> 00:42:34,084
Not bad.

812
00:42:34,351 --> 00:42:36,153
Cardiology's quarterly bonus

813
00:42:36,186 --> 00:42:37,388
is really generous.

814
00:42:37,688 --> 00:42:38,322
Jealous?

815
00:42:39,623 --> 00:42:40,824
I'll treat you to milk tea.

816
00:42:50,834 --> 00:42:51,335
Check your phone.

817
00:42:51,869 --> 00:42:52,770
Check it, check it.

818
00:42:57,041 --> 00:42:58,042
Director Zhou's professional title was promoted.
